\h Yirmeyah
\toc1 Yirmeyah
\toc2 Yirmeyah
\toc3 Yer.
\mt1 Yirmeyah
\mt2 (Jeremiah)
\is1 Introduction
\ip The prophet Yirmeyah/Jeremiah, started his vocation as a prophet around 627 B.C. and continued for just under fifty years until around 580 B.C. Te long time of serving Yirmeyah, impanpanayan he/his the people concerning the destruction coming of nation due to sins their, and of worshipping ran of false gods. And/Now saw of Yirmeyah the katumanan of prophesied he/his of time nasakup e the Yerushalem of Nibukadnisar King of Babylon. Saw/Found his again the demolition of city and temple, and the capture of many people other of King their there to Babylon. Prophesied he/his again the return of people from capture their, and the replacement of standing up of nation there to old natahuan here.
\ip \bk The Account of Yirmeyah\bk* divided of five main sections: 1. The calling to Yirmeyah; 2. the what was said of God for of nation of Yehudah and of teachers here at time of kingdom of Husiyas, Huwakim, Hihuyakin and of Sidikiyas; 3. the all persecution of people according to it's written of Baruk secretary of Yirmeyah, including the various prophecies, and the important what happened of life of Yirmeyah; 4. the what was said of Master God concerning the various foreigner there nations; and 5. the other still story concerning the demolition of Yerushalem, and of pegkaddakep of people going to Babylon.
\ip Merciful person Yirmeyah; very his love the his people, and disliked he/his the judging them. There are parts of document very the love his of telling concerning the sufferings he/his due to because called he of God so that to become prophets. Like fire there to heart he/his the speech of Master God, and not he/his indeed this igkeeles.
\ip Written again of this document coming the time there is e new agreement. And/Now the that agreement eg-ay-ayaran of people of God and obeyed their, even still not/none teacher thinking them because written man e this there to me heart their. (31:31-34)
\iot Main components of this document
\io1 Yirmeyah's calling \ior 1:1-19\ior*
\io1 The prophecies concerning the kingdom of Husiyas, Huwakim, Huwakin, and of Sidikiyas \ior 2:1вҖ“25:38\ior*
\io1 Yirmeyah's persecution \ior 26:1вҖ“45:5\ior*
\io1 The prophecies for nations \ior 46:1вҖ“51:64\ior*
\io1 Yerushalem's destruction \ior 52:1-34\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\p
\v 1 \add These are\add* the messagesВҰ304124 from Hilkiyah's son, YirmeyahвҖ”one of the priestsВҰ304131 who were in AnatotВҰ304133 in Benyamin'sВҰ304135 territoryВҰ304134.
\v 2 Yahweh'sВҰ304141 messagesВҰ304139 \add started\add* coming to him when Yehudah'sВҰ304149 KingВҰ304148 Yoshiyah \add (Josiah,\add* Amon'sВҰ304147 son) was in the thirteenth yearВҰ304153 of his reignВҰ304154.\x + \xo 1:2: \xt 2Ki 22:3вҖ“23:27; 2Ch 34:8вҖ“35:19.\x*
\v 3 \add вүҲIt continued\add* through the \add вүҲreign\add* of Yoshiyah's son, King Yehoyakim \add (Jehoiakim)\add* until the end of the eleventh year of \add the reign\add* of Yoshiyah's son, King Tsidkiyah \add (Hezekiah)\add*вҖ”YerushalemВҰ304179 \add (Jerusalem)\add* was exiledВҰ304178 in the fifthВҰ304181 monthВҰ304180 \add of that year\add*.\x + \xo 1:3: a \xt 2Ki 23:36вҖ“24:7; 2Ch 36:5-8; \xo b \xt 2Ki 24:18вҖ“25:21; 2Ch 36:11-21.\x*
\s1 Yirmeyah's calling
\rem /s1 Jeremiah's Call and First Visions; Jeremiah's call and first visions; Jeremiah's Call and Commission; The Call of Jeremiah
\q1
\v 4 \add вүҲNow\add* Yahweh'sВҰ304187 messageВҰ304185 came to me:
\q1
\v 5 вҖңBeforeВҰ304191 I formedВҰ304192 you in \add вүҲyour mother\add*, I \add already\add* knewВҰ304195 you,
\q1 вүҲand beforeВҰ304196 you cameВҰ304197 out of the womb, I \add вүҲhad a plan for you\add*.
\q1 I appointedВҰ304202 you as a prophetВҰ304200 to the nationsВҰ304201.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲButВҰ304204\add* I saidВҰ304204, вҖңOh no, YahwehВҰ304206, my masterВҰ304206. Listen, I don'tВҰ304209 knowВҰ304211 how to speakВҰ304212, becauseВҰ304214 I'm \add just\add* a young lad.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲbutВҰ304220\add* YahwehВҰ304221 told me, вҖңDon'tВҰ304223 say that you're only a child, becauseВҰ304228 you must goВҰ304235 to everyone I send you to and you must tell them everything that I commandВҰ304240 you to say.
\v 8 Don'tВҰ304243 be afraidВҰ304245 of them, becauseВҰ304247 I'll be with you to rescueВҰ304251 you.вҖқ
\m That's Yahweh'sВҰ304254 messageВҰ304252.
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ304256 YahwehВҰ304257 stretchedВҰ304256 out his handВҰ304260 and touchedВҰ304261 my mouth and said, вҖңListenВҰ304266, I'veВҰ304269 put my messages into your mouth.
\v 10 I'mВҰ304274 appointingВҰ304274 youВҰ304274 today over the nationsВҰ304280 and kingdomsВҰ304283вҖ”to uproot and to break down, to destroyВҰ304286 and to pull down, to buildВҰ304288 and to plantВҰ304289.вҖқ
\s1 Yahweh encourages Yirmeyah
\rem /s1 Two Visions
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲAnother time,\add* Yahweh'sВҰ304295 messageВҰ304293 came to me, saying, вҖңYirmeyah \add (Jeremiah)\add*, what do youВҰ304300 see?вҖқ
\p вҖңI see a branchВҰ304304 from an almondВҰ304305 treeВҰ304305,вҖқ I \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ304309 YahwehВҰ304310 told me, вҖңYou've doneВҰ304312 well to seeВҰ304313 \add <that\add*, becauseВҰ304314 I keep watch\f + \fr 1:12 \ft There's a play on words in the original here, as the Hebrew word for вҖҳkeeping watchвҖҷ has the same consonants as the word for вҖҳalmondвҖҷ.\f* on my messageВҰ304320 \add вүҲto make sure it happens\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 Then YahwehВҰ304327 asked me a secondВҰ304330 time what I was seeing, and I replied, вҖңI see a pot full of boiling water and it's tipping towards the northВҰ304342.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖң\add Yes,\add* disaster will come from the northВҰ304347 \add andВҰ304344\add* be released onto all the inhabitantsВҰ304353 of this region,вҖқ YahwehВҰ304345 \add вүҲcontinuedВҰ304344\add*.
\v 15 вҖңListen, I'm aboutВҰ304359 to summonВҰ304359 all the clansВҰ304362 of the northernВҰ304364 kingdomsВҰ304363, and they'll comeВҰ304368 and \add attack\add* the wallsВҰ304379 aroundВҰ304380 Yerushalem and all of Yehudah'sВҰ304385 \add other\add* citiesВҰ304384, then each \add @king\add* will place his throneВҰ304371 at the entranceВҰ304372 to Yerushalem'sВҰ304375 gatesВҰ304374.вҖқ That is Yahweh'sВҰ304367 declaration.
\v 16 вҖң\add That's how\add* I'llВҰ304387 judgeВҰ304388 \add @my people\add* for their wickednessВҰ304393 as they've abandonedВҰ304395 me and \add вүҲsacrificedВҰ304396\add* to otherВҰ304398 godsВҰ304397 and bowedВҰ304399 down to \add idols\add* thatВҰ304394 they made with their own handsВҰ304401.
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ304403\add* \add @Yirmeyah\add*, \add вүҲget yourself readyВҰ304404 and go\add* and tell them everything that I'll tell you. Don'tВҰ304415 be scaredВҰ304417 \add вүҲin front of them\add* or else I'll scare you \add right there\add* \add вүҲin front of them\add*!
\v 18 And listen, today I'veВҰ304426 youВҰ304426 \add as strong as\add* a fortifiedВҰ304429 cityВҰ304428 and an iron pillarВҰ304430 and bronzeВҰ304433 wallsВҰ304432, as far as the kingsВҰ304439 of YehudahВҰ304440 \add are concerned\add*, along with their officialsВҰ304441 and priestsВҰ304442, and the \add вүҲgeneral population\add*.
\v 19 They'll \add вүҲoppose\add* you \add вүҲbutВҰ304446\add* they won'tВҰ304448 \add be able to\add* defeat you becauseВҰ304452 I'll be with you to rescueВҰ304459 you,вҖқ says YahwehВҰ304458.
\c 2
\s1 Yisrael has deviated from Yahweh
\rem /s1 God's appeal to Israel and Judah; The Lord's Case against His People; God Pleads with Israel to Repent; Israel Forsakes God; God's Care for Israel
\p
